A survey in Shanghai has revealed that one in eight people in the city suffer from overweight. 
 The ratio of adults suffering from obesity has reached 12.6 percent, and that of youngsters is 11.35 percent. 
 The survey indicated that differences in age, gender, and education levels can influence the ratio of obesity. 
 Fifteen percent of female adults suffer from obesity, while the level among male adults is 10.68 percent. 
 The ratio of boys is 14.7 percent, almost double that of girls.